Rating: 4
Delicious and quick once everything is mis en placed. I made this dish with New Zealand cockles and found them a bit too small, so I plan to use little neck clams. I omitted the tomatoes and after the garlic was sauteed, I splashed in about a quarter cup of bottled clam broth and added the clams and covered. I also tossed some fresh parsley over the finished dish. Serve it with a nice french baguette to soak up the juices.